      "writtenOn": "2020-07-30T17:07:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we can guarantee that about line 298. I tried to reason about what happens in that code path, and it\u0027s a circus of creating FPs that get immediately discarded, but I think the final paint color is the original paint color, with alpha set to 1. Then we attach an FP that ends up being a modulation of null (so, input color) by a const-color that is the original paint alpha splatted to all four channels.\n\nThis code (line 298) then ignores the paint color and returns white, so I think *that\u0027s* what the modulation sees when it samples the null input, giving us a final result of [A, A, A, A]. Which all seems to suggest that the paint color RGB is ignored in this case? I may have made an incorrect deduction along the way.",
      "parentUuid": "2e123c91_f2985290",
